The current workaround would be to manually edit the macro (though no changes are needed), save it, and the storage format would be updated. This is a very tedious process, and in the case of a high amount of Issue Macros used, can take a long time.

It would be great if the storage format for the JIRA Issue Macro is updated when the JIRA version that Confluence is linked to is updated, to avoid this from happening.

