When moving pages, there may be some pages have same name which page in target space. Currently, Confluence just show error message that there is a page that duplicate name.

I think we should have a feature that automatically rename colliding pages from the space we're moving things out of, so that we suffix them with " (1)" or 2 etc if that suffix is already in use, truncating the original page title if necessary to keep it under 255 chars. We can then provide a list of pages that collided after we're done moving everything, and help the user to rename these pages to something else should they want to (maybe force any links on this report to open in a new tab, so they can easily come back to it). Any renames will have to update any references as well.

