Confluence is not cleaning the indexqueueentries table in the database, even after successfully running the flush index jobs and cleaning the index queue, the indexqueueentries table rows keep growing without stopping.

This can mean a potential problem in database performance if that table reaches a huge size and it's queried for results.

This was previously stated on this bug https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-17398 but it was closed as fixed.

I'm opening this not as Critical because we have a workaround in place.

h2. Workarounds

h3. MySQL and PostgreSQL
{code:sql}
DELETE FROM indexqueueentries WHERE creationdate < (SELECT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP - interval '2' day);
{code}

h3. Oracle
{code:sql}
DELETE FROM indexqueueentries WHERE creationdate < (SELECT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP - interval '2' day FROM dual);
{code}

h3. MSSQL
{code:sql}
DELETE FROM INDEXQUEUEENTRIES WHERE CREATIONDATE < (SELECT DATEADD(DAY, -2, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP));
{code}

